  "prompt": "Do anti-money laundering regulations exist?",
  "response": "Yes, anti-money laundering (AML) regulations exist in many countries. These laws are designed to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income. Key examples include:\n\n1. United States: Bank Secrecy Act (BSA) and USA PATRIOT Act\n2. European Union: Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n3. United Kingdom: Proceeds of Crime Act\n4. International standards set by Financial Action Task Force (FATF)\n\nFinancial institutions are typically required to:\n- Verify customer identities\n- Report suspicious transactions\n- Maintain transaction records\n- Implement compliance programs\n\nThese regulations aim to combat financial crimes like drug trafficking, terrorism financing, and fraud.",
